        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 3:12PM CDT by NWS Kansas City/Pleasant Hill MO</headline>
        <description>At 312 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Windsor to Urich to near Adrian. Movement
was east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Clinton, Urich, Calhoun, Creighton, Blairstown, Ballard, Hartwell,
and La Due.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for
west central Missouri.</instruction>
